<p>Jan Engelhardt is an independent IT Consultant from Central Germany.</p>

<p>With about 12 years of experience in working with Linux server systems,
he has come to dedicate himself to distribution packaging and writing
kernel/system-level software. He is primarily active in the field of
Networking and is the lead contributor to the Xtables/iptables packet
filter. He has also resurrected the openSUSE port to the SPARC
architecture in 2009.</p>
